<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.native-languages.org/dictionary.htm
">Indian Language Dictionaries</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Omaha-Ponca and other American Indian dictionaries and language materials for sale.
<BR>

<H2>
Omaha-Ponca Language Lessons and Linguistic Descriptions</H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://spot.colorado.edu/~koontz/omaha/op_sketch.htm
">Omaha-Ponca</a></b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Excellent information on the Omaha-Ponca language presented by Siouan linguist John Koontz.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.turtletrack.org/Issues03/Co12132003/CO_12132003_OmahaLanguage.htm
">Omaha language classes keep culture alive</a></b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Article on language preservation in the Omaha tribe.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
https://web.archive.org/web/20091027141347/http://www.geocities.com/Athens/9479/lakota.html#oma
">Sioux Placenames</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Chart of place names in Omaha-Ponca and <a href="http://www.native-languages.org/dakota.htm">Lakota-Dakota</a>.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.hello-oklahoma.com/ponca.htm
">Hello Oklahoma: Ponca Tribe</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Ponca language greeting, alphabet, and text.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.language-museum.com/encyclopedia/o/omaha-ponca.php
">Language Museum: Omaha-Ponca</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Omaha language sample.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.ethnologue.com/show_language.asp?code=oma
">Omaha-Ponca Language</a></b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Demographic information about Omaha-Ponca from the Ethnologue of Languages.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://multitree.org/codes/oma.html
">Omaha-Ponca Language Tree</a>:</b> <br> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Theories about Ponca and Omaha language relationships compiled by Linguist List.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://wals.info/languoid/lect/wals_code_omh
">Omaha Language Structures</a>:</b> <br> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Omaha-Ponca linguistic profile and academic bibliography.
